# Echothink-Patch: 0016-chat-panel-shell
# Title: Add the Echothink Side Panel Chat shell with scope metadata
# Area: extension
# Depends-On: echothink/0004-bundled-workspace-extension.patch, echothink/0014-side-panel-container.patch, echothink/0015-side-panel-mode-selector.patch
# Browser-Layer-Reason: The bundled Side Panel needs a browser-local Chat UI shell that can send the user's selected Alpha scope metadata to the protected Echothink chat gateway. Keeping this in the MV3 extension avoids native Chromium UI rewrites and keeps conversation persistence/model orchestration outside the browser.
# Preferred-Surface-Checked: extension (local sidepanel.html/sidepanel.css/sidepanel.js UI and fetch to the existing Echothink API host permission)
# Security-Critical-Areas: none
# Native-Files-Touched: chrome/browser/resources/echothink_workspace/sidepanel.html, chrome/browser/resources/echothink_workspace/sidepanel.css, chrome/browser/resources/echothink_workspace/sidepanel.js
# Rebase-Risk: low (updates only bundled extension resource files added by echothink/0004)
# Validation: Apply inherited patches, then echothink/0001..0005 and later tail patches including echothink/0014, echothink/0015, and this patch with `patch -p1` against pinned Chromium 148.0.7778.178; launch a fresh profile, open Chat mode, verify the scope selector is visible, submit a message against a test chat endpoint, and verify the JSON body includes `scope.scope_type`.
#
# Notes:
# - Chat requests use `POST https://api.echothink.ai/v1/chat/stream` with
#   `credentials: "include"` and selected scope metadata in the JSON body.
# - The UI never reads, renders, or logs private key material, access tokens, or
#   proof internals. Request proof integration remains a later task.
# - Conversation persistence and model orchestration remain remote. The browser
#   keeps only the current in-memory panel transcript.

